WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.300 --> 00:00:04.140
- Ned Fulmer is no longer
working with the Try Guys.

00:00:04.140 --> 00:00:06.810
By now, we're assuming you've
seen the Reddit threads,

00:00:06.810 --> 00:00:10.710
and TikToks, and tweets,
and news articles.

00:00:10.710 --> 00:00:13.020
We want to give you a
timeline of what's transpired

00:00:13.020 --> 00:00:16.740
and some transparency
into our decision making.

00:00:16.740 --> 00:00:17.573
Throughout this video,

00:00:17.573 --> 00:00:21.270
there will be things that we
want to say or go into further,

00:00:21.270 --> 00:00:24.390
but as I'm sure you're aware,
there are some legal issues

00:00:24.390 --> 00:00:26.793
we have to consider as
we go through everything.

00:00:27.990 --> 00:00:30.630
- On Labor Day weekend,
multiple fans alerted us

00:00:30.630 --> 00:00:33.120
that they had seen Ned and an employee

00:00:33.120 --> 00:00:35.640
engaging in public romantic behavior.

00:00:35.640 --> 00:00:38.040
We reached out to check on that employee.

00:00:38.040 --> 00:00:41.370
Ned confirmed the reports
and since confirmed

00:00:41.370 --> 00:00:43.110
that this had been going on for some time,

00:00:43.110 --> 00:00:45.240
which was obviously very shocking to us.

00:00:45.240 --> 00:00:46.590
And we just want you to know that

00:00:46.590 --> 00:00:48.330
we had no idea this was going on.

00:00:48.330 --> 00:00:50.880
All of that information
was just as shocking to us

00:00:50.880 --> 00:00:52.980
as all of this has been for you this week.

00:00:53.850 --> 00:00:56.550
- And thus began a three
week process of engaging with

00:00:56.550 --> 00:01:00.540
employment lawyers, corporate
lawyers, HR, PR, and more

00:01:00.540 --> 00:01:03.630
in order to make sure we were
taking all necessary steps.

00:01:03.630 --> 00:01:06.180
From the jump, we were acutely aware

00:01:06.180 --> 00:01:08.310
of just how contrary this was

00:01:08.310 --> 00:01:10.320
to the values of the company we've built

00:01:10.320 --> 00:01:12.170
and those of everyone who works here.

00:01:13.320 --> 00:01:18.320
This is something we took very seriously.

00:01:18.750 --> 00:01:22.140
We refused to sweep things under the rug.

00:01:22.140 --> 00:01:26.070
That is not who we are and
is not what we stand for.

00:01:26.070 --> 00:01:28.950
- We immediately removed
Ned from work activities

00:01:28.950 --> 00:01:30.870
and engaged an HR professional

00:01:30.870 --> 00:01:33.990
to conduct a thorough review of the facts.

00:01:33.990 --> 00:01:36.600
We also opted to remove
Ned from our releases

00:01:36.600 --> 00:01:39.630
pending the results of that review.

00:01:39.630 --> 00:01:42.360
Over a few weeks, that's
included removing his section

00:01:42.360 --> 00:01:45.360
from videos, digitally
removing him from others,

00:01:45.360 --> 00:01:47.970
and choosing not to feature
him in our merch throws.

00:01:47.970 --> 00:01:50.940
Honestly, I want to give major
props to our editing staff

00:01:50.940 --> 00:01:53.160
for how deftly they've handled that.

00:01:53.160 --> 00:01:54.210
There are several videos

00:01:54.210 --> 00:01:56.070
that we've deemed as fully unreleasable.

00:01:56.070 --> 00:01:58.980
You will never see them and
that is due to his involvement.

00:01:58.980 --> 00:02:02.610
And that's a decision that
has cost us lots of money.

00:02:02.610 --> 00:02:03.960
We will not be able to recoup that money,

00:02:03.960 --> 00:02:05.960
but it's a decision we stand by proudly.

00:02:06.900 --> 00:02:09.240
- Now, we can't talk about
the details of the review,

00:02:09.240 --> 00:02:13.170
but suffice to say we found
that Ned had engaged in contact,

00:02:13.170 --> 00:02:15.690
well, conduct unbecoming of our team

00:02:15.690 --> 00:02:18.600
and we knew that we could
not move forward with him.

00:02:18.600 --> 00:02:20.640
So on Friday, September 16th,

00:02:20.640 --> 00:02:23.370
the three of us signed written consent

00:02:23.370 --> 00:02:25.470
of the members of Second Try LLC

00:02:25.470 --> 00:02:28.923
approving the removal of Ned
as a manager and an employee.

00:02:29.880 --> 00:02:32.130
We chose not to rush into the announcement

00:02:32.130 --> 00:02:33.150
for a few reasons.

00:02:33.150 --> 00:02:36.180
Namely, there are real people
who have been affected.

00:02:36.180 --> 00:02:39.030
And while we consider
this a company matter,

00:02:39.030 --> 00:02:41.493
there's just also a family
at the center of this.

00:02:42.720 --> 00:02:45.870
- Now we were always planning
on a public statement

00:02:45.870 --> 00:02:47.850
and we're working towards
that with our team.

00:02:47.850 --> 00:02:51.330
But in light of rapidly
accelerating speculation,

00:02:51.330 --> 00:02:54.420
we knew we couldn't wait any longer.

00:02:54.420 --> 00:02:56.340
We were obviously incredibly shocked

00:02:56.340 --> 00:02:58.380
and deeply hurt by all of this.

00:02:58.380 --> 00:03:00.540
This is someone who we'd built a brand

00:03:00.540 --> 00:03:03.513
and a company with for eight years.

00:03:06.240 --> 00:03:08.670
We feel saddened, not just personally,

00:03:08.670 --> 00:03:13.020
but on behalf of our staff and
our fans who believed in us.

00:03:13.020 --> 00:03:15.240
- I don't know that we'll
ever be able to fully

00:03:15.240 --> 00:03:17.370
articulate the pain we
feel at this moment.

00:03:17.370 --> 00:03:19.860
It's hard to rewatch old videos

00:03:19.860 --> 00:03:21.090
that we love and are proud of.

00:03:21.090 --> 00:03:22.560
We're losing a friend,

00:03:22.560 --> 00:03:24.870
we're losing someone we
we built a company with,

00:03:24.870 --> 00:03:26.760
we have countless memories with.

00:03:26.760 --> 00:03:28.980
We just made a TV show together.

00:03:28.980 --> 00:03:31.770
I'm sure many of you feel the same way.

00:03:31.770 --> 00:03:32.603
It's weird.

00:03:32.603 --> 00:03:34.230
We're sorry that this ever happened

00:03:34.230 --> 00:03:36.450
and we don't know what more to say.

00:03:36.450 --> 00:03:39.360
- This is also our staff of 20 strong who,

00:03:39.360 --> 00:03:41.010
they just don't deserve
the negative attention

00:03:41.010 --> 00:03:44.100
our brand is now getting
'cause they didn't do anything.

00:03:44.100 --> 00:03:45.540
But they're our family and
they're some of the most

00:03:45.540 --> 00:03:47.430
talented creative minds in the world

00:03:47.430 --> 00:03:49.500
and our primary focus
right now is making sure

00:03:49.500 --> 00:03:51.840
they feel comfortable
and proud coming to work.

00:03:51.840 --> 00:03:54.630
The work they do never
ceases to astound us

00:03:54.630 --> 00:03:56.310
and frankly, there's just no world

00:03:56.310 --> 00:03:59.640
in which we could have navigated
all of this without them.

00:03:59.640 --> 00:04:01.590
Now, there are videos that were shot

00:04:01.590 --> 00:04:02.790
ahead of all this, right?

00:04:02.790 --> 00:04:04.170
We're gonna be editing Ned out

00:04:04.170 --> 00:04:05.910
like the new season of "Without A Recipe"

00:04:05.910 --> 00:04:07.380
and we're working with our editors

00:04:07.380 --> 00:04:10.050
in finding creative
solutions to the footage.

00:04:10.050 --> 00:04:11.700
And we also have some branded videos

00:04:11.700 --> 00:04:13.080
that we've already committed to.

00:04:13.080 --> 00:04:14.340
So when you see a video

00:04:14.340 --> 00:04:15.810
that's sponsored in a few
weeks and you're like,

00:04:15.810 --> 00:04:18.177
oh, that's kind of weird, well,
yeah, it is kind of weird.

00:04:18.177 --> 00:04:20.733
It's just how things are and that's why.

00:04:22.290 --> 00:04:24.690
- Look, I get that when
stuff like this happens,

00:04:24.690 --> 00:04:27.360
there's going to be speculation and gossip

00:04:27.360 --> 00:04:29.400
and we ask that you respect the privacy

00:04:29.400 --> 00:04:31.380
of the family members and employees

00:04:31.380 --> 00:04:33.240
who may be caught up in this.

00:04:33.240 --> 00:04:35.460
We also wanna remind you that the internet

00:04:35.460 --> 00:04:40.110
has a tendency to be a lot
harsher towards women than men.

00:04:40.110 --> 00:04:43.950
So please, we ask that
you exercise kindness.

00:04:43.950 --> 00:04:46.200
- Things will change here.

00:04:46.200 --> 00:04:47.850
What we hope is that within this,

00:04:47.850 --> 00:04:50.760
there's also the opportunity
for positive growth

00:04:50.760 --> 00:04:53.613
and better videos ahead,
but it's gonna be hard.

00:04:54.540 --> 00:04:57.000
This whole thing is gonna
be really fuckin' hard.

00:04:57.000 --> 00:04:58.770
- And we imagine you
have lots of questions,

00:04:58.770 --> 00:05:00.270
lot more questions right now

00:05:00.270 --> 00:05:02.820
and we're gonna have more
to say in the future,

00:05:02.820 --> 00:05:03.930
just right now we're focused on

00:05:03.930 --> 00:05:05.370
bringing the best content possible

00:05:05.370 --> 00:05:08.160
between now and the end of
the year and then figuring out

00:05:08.160 --> 00:05:10.860
what the future of this
channel looks like from there.

00:05:12.690 --> 00:05:13.740
- That's it for now.

00:05:13.740 --> 00:05:15.600
Again, more to come.

00:05:15.600 --> 00:05:17.970
Some things may change.

00:05:17.970 --> 00:05:22.260
We are just sort of figuring
it out all one day at a time.

00:05:22.260 --> 00:05:23.970
- Thank you for your support.

00:05:23.970 --> 00:05:27.570
We appreciate you and we look forward to

00:05:27.570 --> 00:05:30.693
introducing you to the next
era of the Try Guys ahead.

